DESCRIPTION:Loved by The Telegraph ("the best improv I've ever seen!")\, Br
 itish Comedy Guide ("consistently slick") and our mums ("very polite")\, Gi
 ddy Aunt Improv is improv done right. Fast\, frenetic and joyfully silly - 
 made up on the spot - with songs\, sketches\, and boundless scenarios. Foll
 owing 5 sell-out years at the Leicester Comedy Festival\, they bring their 
 award nominated show to the Camden Fringe for a night full of pints\, laugh
 s and just a lovely time had by all. Do pop by! Nominated for Best Variety 
 Show 2026 (Leicester Comedy Festival). Which is nice.\nMore info: https://c
 omedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/giddy-aunt-improv/
